The article discusses the positive impact of music therapy on soldiers with traumatic brain injuries. The author, Karen Pence, shares her experience of being serenaded by four servicemen at a music therapy session at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Anchorage, Alaska. The soldiers testified to the dramatic improvements in their lives, including memory enhancement, anger reduction, tremor control, and speech recovery. The success of the 6-week progressive music therapy group is highlighted, with numerous stories of lives being put back together. Music therapy is said to increase concentration, emotional expression, rhythmic entrainment, and overall brain function. The author expresses gratitude to the music therapist, Danielle Kalseth, and the soldiers who shared their music. Karen Pence also emphasizes her commitment to promoting art therapy through her initiative, Art Therapy: Healing with the HeART.